main event: A civilian witness observed an unidentified object in the sky for 30-40 seconds on October 8, 1966 in East Dennis, Massachusetts.
interesting points: The report indicates 'INSUFFICIENT DATA FOR EVALUATION', suggesting there was not enough information provided to properly assess the sighting.
The report references 'PROJECT 10073 RECORD' and 'PROJECT BLUE BOOK', indicating this was part of the U.S. Air Force's historical UFO investigation program.
The report contains various data points such as height, pressure, temperature, direction, and speed, likely related to analysis of the reported sighting.
A letter from Major Quintanilla, the Chief of Project Blue Book, requests the witness complete an additional form to aid in the scientific evaluation of the sighting.
The report does not contain any photographs, despite the 'PHOTOS' field being present on the form.
